<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> make free of something • make free with something</xh5><p> <i>make free of something—</i>be allowed or have the right to use smth. that belongs to smb. else: In some cases a couple would actually build for themselves a single cottage, but as a rule they were content to <u>make free of</u> each other’s private homes. </p><p><i>make free with something—</i>use smth. that belongs to smb. else without permission or in a way that is considered unacceptable: They walked home, along with their friends, and <u>made free with</u> my house and kitchen whilst I was busy being a dinner lady at school.</p> </entry>
